Table ‘user’ users. Displays all users of the site.
Table ‘basket’ basket. Shows added to the basket of goods, their number, and users who have ordered them.

Table ‘document’ documents. CMS folders. Displays the basic structure of the site. Right-clicking on the selected folder - to create, edit, view, delete this folder. Left-clicking on the selected folder - to create, edit, view, delete elements in this folder.

Table ‘document’ documents. Elements of a specific folder. These can be publications, products, letter templates, or your own elements used on the site. To create, edit, view, delete items, select a folder.
Table ‘template’ templates. contains templates for items. Templates are assigned to folders and applied to the elements of these folders.
Tables ‘source_message’ source text and category, and ‘message’ their translation. Multilingual management.
Country ‘geo_country’ table. Contains a list of countries and information about them.
Table ‘city geo_city’. Contains a list of cities and information about them.
Table ‘geo_region’ regions. Contains a list of regions and information about them.
